<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,151,255]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,320,151,177]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</emphasis>
Members of 
<taxonomicName box="[484,607,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Platyledra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[484,607,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Platyledra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are defined by their acuminate crowns and dorsoventrally depressed pronota bearing a single medial longitudinal crest. They form a monophyletic group (the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1907" box="[1247,1356,191,216]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Jukaruka" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1247,1356,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Jukaruka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus group) with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1907" box="[296,405,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Jukaruka" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[296,405,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Jukaruka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fletcher" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[461,600,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Ledropsella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[461,600,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Ledropsella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
